WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.738
HEY, LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY
LANDED A NEW CLIENT.

00:04.738 --> 00:06.074
THIS IS ALL CUSTOM STUFF

00:06.074 --> 00:07.641
FOR A WEDDING I'M PLANNING
FOR THIS WEEKEND.

00:07.641 --> 00:10.478
WHOA, WHAT'S THIS,
A BELT FOR A WEDDING DRESS?

00:15.983 --> 00:17.818
NO, IT'S A GARTER.

00:17.818 --> 00:20.488
I GOT A PLUS-SIZE BRIDE.

00:22.690 --> 00:26.594
IT IS A BRAVE MAN WHO GOES
TO GET THIS OFF WITH HIS TEETH.

00:29.697 --> 00:31.699
HEY, GEORGE,
THAT'S NOT RIGHT, MAN.

00:31.699 --> 00:33.234
MY MOM'S A PLUS-SIZE LADY,

00:33.234 --> 00:36.137
AND SHE'S BEAUTIFUL
AND FULL OF LIFE.

00:36.137 --> 00:38.606
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
SHE GOT OUT OF BED?

00:38.606 --> 00:41.809
WELL, IT'S HARD TO TELL.
SHE WEARS SHEETS AS CLOTHES NOW.

00:44.044 --> 00:45.213
HEY, MOM.

00:45.213 --> 00:46.714
HEY, HONEY,
HOW WAS SCHOOL?

00:46.714 --> 00:49.049
IT FINALLY HAPPENED.
I'M OUT OF SPECIAL ED.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.618
THEY PUT ME BACK
IN REGULAR CLASSES!

00:50.618 --> 00:53.154
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE, MAN?
YOU CAN'T EVEN --

00:53.154 --> 00:55.556
HEY, CONGRATULATIONS.

00:55.556 --> 00:57.758
I TOOK THE PROFICIENCY TEST
AND I PASSED.

00:57.758 --> 00:59.527
SEE? THAT'S THE WAY
THE LOPEZES DO IT.

00:59.527 --> 01:01.962
WE FAIL, WE FAIL,
WE FAIL, WE FAIL,

01:01.962 --> 01:04.532
UNTIL ONE DAY, BOOM,
WE'VE AVERAGE.

01:07.101 --> 01:11.239
HEY, GRANDMA, GUESS WHAT?
I'M NOT IN SPECIAL ED ANYMORE.

01:11.239 --> 01:14.108
OH, MAX, THAT IS GREAT!

01:14.108 --> 01:16.510
IS THERE SOMETHING WORSE
THAN SPECIAL ED?

01:19.347 --> 01:23.717
WHY IS EVERYONE SO SURPRISED
MAX IS DOING BETTER?

01:23.717 --> 01:26.754
HE'S LEARNING TO DEAL
WITH HIS DYSLEXIA.

01:26.754 --> 01:28.989
HE'S A VERY SMART BOY.

01:28.989 --> 01:30.658
YOU GOT A 60?

01:30.658 --> 01:33.527
WELL, 60 -- THAT'S THE SCORE
YOU GOT LAST YEAR

01:33.527 --> 01:35.263
THAT KEPT YOU IN SPECIAL ED.

01:35.263 --> 01:37.698
I KNOW, BUT THE SCHOOL
CHANGED THE RULES.

01:37.698 --> 01:39.300
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
THEY CHANGED THE RULES?

01:39.300 --> 01:41.469
IT'S IN THIS LETTER.

01:41.469 --> 01:43.837
MY SPECIAL-ED TEACHER
SAYS IT'S A TRAGEDY

01:43.837 --> 01:45.839
AND I'LL PROBABLY FALL
THROUGH THE CRACKS.

01:45.839 --> 01:47.175
BUT WHAT DOES SHE KNOW?

01:47.175 --> 01:49.243
SHE'S NOT SMART ENOUGH
TO TEACH REGULAR KIDS.

01:52.680 --> 01:56.517
YOU KNOW, THEY SAID THAT I WAS
GONNA FALL THROUGH THE CRACKS.

01:56.517 --> 01:58.719
YEAH, THEY JUST KEPT PASSING ME
FROM GRADE TO GRADE,

01:58.719 --> 02:02.656
BUT, HEH, I TURNED OUT
PRETTY SUCCESSFUL.

02:02.656 --> 02:05.025
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:05.025 --> 02:08.329
WELL, I BETTER
GO TO THE FACTORY.

02:08.329 --> 02:12.500
IT'S MY TURN TO RIP THE RAT LEGS
OFF THE STICKY TRAPS.

02:12.500 --> 02:14.134
LATER.

02:15.936 --> 02:18.506
WHAT DO I ALWAYS SAY, MAX?

02:18.506 --> 02:21.475
ERNIE'S NOT A ROLE MODEL.

02:21.475 --> 02:24.412
THAT'S RIGHT.
HE'S MORE LIKE A CLOWN, BUT...

02:24.412 --> 02:27.014
NOT ALL CLOWNS ARE SAD.
VERY GOOD.

02:27.014 --> 02:28.716
THIS IS TERRIBLE.

02:28.716 --> 02:30.718
THEY'RE TRYING TO SAVE MONEY
BY MAINSTREAMING

02:30.718 --> 02:32.753
A BUNCH OF KIDS
THAT AREN'T READY FOR IT.

02:32.753 --> 02:35.489
MAX IS BEING FORCED OUT
OF A PROGRAM HE STILL NEEDS.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.258
THIS LETTER SAYS
IT'S A DISTRICT POLICY,

02:37.258 --> 02:38.726
BUT IF WE WANT
MORE INFORMATION,

02:38.726 --> 02:40.093
THERE'S A SCHOOL-BOARD MEETING
TOMORROW NIGHT.

02:40.093 --> 02:41.962
WELL, WE'RE GOING,

02:41.962 --> 02:44.832
AND THEY'RE GOING TO LISTEN TO
ME BECAUSE I'M A GOOD CITIZEN,

02:44.832 --> 02:46.166
AND I PAY MY TAXES.

02:46.166 --> 02:50.438
I MAY CLAIM
A FEW EXTRA DEPENDANTS.

02:50.438 --> 02:52.105
BUT WHEN YOU'RE LATINO

02:52.105 --> 02:56.310
AND YOU HAVE LESS THAN 10
SABÃ©S QUE, THAT'S A RED FLAG.

02:56.310 --> 02:59.347
THE MEETING
STARTS AT 8:00.

02:59.347 --> 03:00.848
HONEY, LOOK AT THIS.

03:00.848 --> 03:03.617
THE MEETING'S BEING RUN
BY YOUR SISTER.

03:03.617 --> 03:05.286
George:
YOU'RE KIDDING.

03:05.286 --> 03:07.255
"LINDA LORENZO,
SUPERINTENDENT OF SCHOOLS."

03:07.255 --> 03:08.822
HUH.

03:08.822 --> 03:10.824
TOO BAD SHE DOESN'T KNOW
YOU'RE HER BROTHER.

03:10.824 --> 03:12.493
SHE COULD REALLY HELP
WITH MAX.

03:12.493 --> 03:14.061
HEY, WOULD YOU STOP IT?

03:14.061 --> 03:15.763
SHE DOESN'T KNOW
SHE'S ADOPTED,

03:15.763 --> 03:17.631
AND I DON'T WANT HER BACK
IN MY LIFE NOW ANYWAY.

03:17.631 --> 03:22.536
THE LAST TIME I SAW HER,
SHE WAS ALL CRYING AND NEEDY.

03:22.536 --> 03:26.907
SHE WAS 4 DAYS OLD.

03:28.776 --> 03:30.878
PEOPLE DON'T CHANGE.

03:30.878 --> 03:32.780
RELAX, MOM.

03:32.780 --> 03:34.848
I DIDN'T TELL HER
SHE WAS MY SISTER LAST TIME,

03:34.848 --> 03:36.584
AND I'M NOT GONNA
TELL HER THIS TIME

03:36.584 --> 03:38.919
BECAUSE HOW DO YOU EXPLAIN
TO A BEAUTIFUL YOUNG WOMAN

03:38.919 --> 03:41.054
THAT WHEN IT ALL
STARTS TO GO...

03:41.054 --> 03:43.891
THAT'S HOW FAR IT GOES?

03:45.759 --> 03:48.061
I JUST LOOKED AT MY FIRST
HOMEWORK FOR REGULAR CLASSES,

03:48.061 --> 03:50.464
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW
I'M GONNA DO THE BEST I CAN.

03:50.464 --> 03:54.101
BUT THERE'S GONNA BE CHEATING.

03:54.101 --> 03:55.769
LOTS OF IT.

03:58.739 --> 04:01.275
[ INTRO TO WAR'S "LOW RIDER"
PLAYS ]

04:04.878 --> 04:10.451
* ALL MY FRIENDS
KNOW THE LOW RIDER *

04:12.486 --> 04:16.857
* THE LOW RIDER
IS A LITTLE HIGHER *

04:32.906 --> 04:35.776
WELL, THEY DON'T HAVE
MONEY FOR SPECIAL ED,

04:35.776 --> 04:39.012
BUT THEY GOT MONEY FOR URINALS
THAT FLUSH THEMSELVES.

04:39.012 --> 04:41.715
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

04:41.715 --> 04:44.352
WHY ARE YOU
OUT OF BREATH?

04:44.352 --> 04:46.520
I GOT THEM
ALL GOING AT ONCE.

04:49.690 --> 04:52.893
IT SOUNDED
LIKE A WATERFALL.

04:52.893 --> 04:56.897
AND THEN THE SOUND OF THE WATER
MADE ME HAVE TO GO AGAIN.

04:58.231 --> 05:00.300
[ SIGHS ]

05:00.300 --> 05:02.102
ISN'T THAT YOUR SISTER?

05:02.102 --> 05:05.072
YEAH, I'M GOING TO RUN UP THERE
AND SEE IF SHE REMEMBERS ME.

05:05.072 --> 05:08.275
LAST TIME I TOLD HER I
WAS INVOLVED WITH SOME
PHONY DYSLEXIC ORGANIZATION,

05:08.275 --> 05:09.877
AND WE BONDED A LITTLE BIT.

05:09.877 --> 05:12.880
OOH, OOH. HERE. BEFORE YOU GO,
THIS MAY HELP OUR CASE.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.748
MAX WROTE A LETTER
TO THE SCHOOL BOARD

05:14.748 --> 05:17.651
ABOUT WHY HE WANTS
TO STAY IN REGULAR CLASSES.

05:17.651 --> 05:20.388
"DEAR SIR OR MAD MAN...

05:23.424 --> 05:25.726
"...I DESERVE TO STAY
IN REGULAR CLASSES,

05:25.726 --> 05:28.529
AND HERE ARE
MY POT FIVE RAISINS."

05:28.529 --> 05:31.465
GOD, WE LET THIS KID
USE A KNIFE AT DINNER?

05:31.465 --> 05:32.533
JUST GO.
JUST GO.

05:32.533 --> 05:35.268
HI. LINDA?

05:35.268 --> 05:38.005
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU REMEMBER ME.
I'M GEORGE LOPEZ.

05:38.005 --> 05:39.807
I'M WITH THE FCD,

05:39.807 --> 05:43.377
THE FEDERATION
OF CHICANO DYSLEXICS.

05:43.377 --> 05:45.012
YES, I DO REMEMBER YOU,

05:45.012 --> 05:46.980
BUT LAST TIME YOU SAID
YOU WERE WITH L.A.D.,

05:46.980 --> 05:49.116
LATINO ASSOCIATION
FOR DYSLEXICS.

05:49.116 --> 05:52.252
RIGHT.

05:52.252 --> 05:55.423
YEAH, YOU KNOW, WE HAD
A BIG FIGHT AT OUR SPELLING BEE,

05:55.423 --> 05:57.491
SO NOW WE GOT

05:57.491 --> 06:01.429
A WHOLE EAST-COAST,
WEST-COAST DYSLEXIC FEUD.

06:01.429 --> 06:03.964
AND IT'S LIKE THE RAP THING
BUT WORSE

06:03.964 --> 06:07.768
'CAUSE WE'RE DYSLEXIC SO WE
DON'T KNOW WHAT COAST WE'RE ON.

06:07.768 --> 06:09.837
ANYWAY, LOOK, I'M HERE
TO TALK ABOUT MY SON, MAX.

06:09.837 --> 06:11.705
HE'S DYSLEXIC,
AND HE'S BEING PUSHED

06:11.705 --> 06:13.340
OUT OF
HIS SPECIAL-ED PROGRAM.

06:13.340 --> 06:15.676
I UNDERSTAND WHY YOU'RE
CONCERNED. IT'S ON THE AGENDA.

06:15.676 --> 06:17.745
IF WE DON'T GET TO IT
AT TONIGHT'S MEETING,

06:17.745 --> 06:19.480
WE'LL DEFINITELY GET TO IT
AT NEXT MONTH'S.

06:19.480 --> 06:22.583
NEXT MONTH?
MY SON'S GONNA FALL WAY BEHIND.

06:22.583 --> 06:23.917
LOOK, READ THIS,
AND KEEP IN MIND

06:23.917 --> 06:27.421
THIS IS NOT A MONKEY,
THIS IS A HUMAN CHILD.

06:27.421 --> 06:29.757
IT'S JUST
THAT EVERY PARENT HERE

06:29.757 --> 06:31.792
HAS SOMETHING
THAT THEY WANT TO DISCUSS.

06:31.792 --> 06:34.895
HERE'S THE WEIRD THING
ABOUT THAT -- I DON'T CARE.

06:34.895 --> 06:38.966
LOOK, MR. LOPEZ, WE WILL GET
TO YOU WHEN WE GET TO YOU.

06:38.966 --> 06:42.135
YEAH,
BUT MY KID WROTE DOWN --
PLEASE SIT DOWN.

06:42.135 --> 06:44.672
BUT --
SIT DOWN!

06:44.672 --> 06:47.541
[ Mockingly ]
SIT DOWN.

06:47.541 --> 06:49.443
"WE'LL GET TO YOU
WHEN WE GET TO YOU."

06:49.443 --> 06:51.612
I HATE MY SISTER, ANGIE.
I HATE HER SO MUCH.

06:51.612 --> 06:53.447
I WISH I WAS
AN ONLY CHILD AGAIN.

06:54.815 --> 06:58.018
GOOD EVENING. I'M LINDA LORENZO,
SUPERINTENDENT.

06:58.018 --> 07:00.387
WE HAVE A VERY FULL AGENDA
FOR THIS EVENING'S MEETING,

07:00.387 --> 07:02.122
SO LET'S GO AHEAD
AND GET STARTED.

07:02.122 --> 07:04.391
WHO CARES, EH?

07:04.391 --> 07:06.059
ITEM NUMBER ONE --

07:06.059 --> 07:08.929
THE IMPROVEMENTS
TO THE DRUG-PREVENTION PROGRAM.

07:08.929 --> 07:10.731
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WE GET IT, ALL RIGHT?

07:10.731 --> 07:12.733
HUGS NOT DRUGS,
CRACK IS WHACK.

07:12.733 --> 07:14.768
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT'S NUMBER TWO?

07:14.768 --> 07:16.236
'CAUSE YOU KNOW
THE INNER CITY, RIGHT?

07:16.236 --> 07:19.272
ARE YOU GUYS MARILYN McCOO
AND BILLY DAVIS JR.?

07:19.272 --> 07:22.643
Shh. GEORGE.
WHAT?

07:22.643 --> 07:24.645
MR. LOPEZ, I KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT.

07:24.645 --> 07:25.679
WOULD YOU PLEASE
SIT DOWN AND WAIT?

07:25.679 --> 07:27.247
I'M NOT GONNA SIT DOWN.

07:27.247 --> 07:29.717
WE'RE THE PARENTS, AND WE'RE
THE ONES WHO PAY TAXES!

07:29.717 --> 07:32.052
YEAH, AND I WANT TO TALK
ABOUT SCHOOL LUNCHES.

07:32.052 --> 07:34.522
MY CHILD'S A VEGAN, AND YOU COOK
YOUR FRENCH FRIES IN ANIMAL FAT.

07:34.522 --> 07:36.156
WHAT ABOUT THAT?

07:36.156 --> 07:38.759
WHAT THE?

07:41.128 --> 07:44.832
TAXI DRIVER,
SIT YOUR ASS DOWN.

07:44.832 --> 07:47.467
WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT LEARNING HERE!

07:47.467 --> 07:50.137
IF YOU DON'T SIT DOWN, I'M GONNA
HAVE TO HAVE YOU REMOVED.

07:50.137 --> 07:52.740
I'M NOT GONNA SIT DOWN
UNTIL MY SON GETS THE
HELP THAT HE NEEDS,

07:52.740 --> 07:56.143
AND I DARE SOMEBODY
TO MAKE A MOVE BECAUSE
I'M FROM THE STREET.

07:56.143 --> 07:57.745
SECURITY!

07:57.745 --> 07:59.246
GEORGE, SIT DOWN!

07:59.246 --> 08:01.048
THAT'S THE PROBLEM
WITH THE SCHOOL SYSTEM, ANGIE.

08:01.048 --> 08:04.084
I KNOW. I GOT BOOKS,
EVEN THOUGH I HAVEN'T READ THEM.

08:04.084 --> 08:08.321
TALKING ABOUT PLAYGROUNDS AND
VEGETABLES AND LANGUAGE LABS.

08:08.321 --> 08:09.890
THIS IS L.A.

08:09.890 --> 08:12.025
YOU WANT TO LEARN SPANISH,
TAKE A BUS!

08:12.025 --> 08:15.829
LOOK, I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE
TILL YOU HELP MY SON!

08:15.829 --> 08:18.566
WHY SHOULD I GIVE YOUR CHILD
MORE HELP THAN ANYBODY ELSE'S?

08:18.566 --> 08:20.200
BECAUSE HE'S YOUR NEPHEW!

08:21.535 --> 08:22.235
AND I'M YOUR BROTHER!

08:22.235 --> 08:23.837
WHAT?

08:23.837 --> 08:26.506
THAT'S RIGHT! YOU'RE
THROWING OUT YOUR OWN BROTHER!

08:26.506 --> 08:28.909
ASK YOUR PARENTS
ABOUT BENNY LOPEZ!

08:28.909 --> 08:31.344
I'M A NAVY SEAL.
IF WE TAKE THIS TO THE POOL --

08:31.344 --> 08:33.480
OW, MY VACCINE!

08:33.480 --> 08:34.847
GEORGE.

08:43.390 --> 08:44.858
[ YAWNS ]

08:50.363 --> 08:51.565
[ SIGHS ]

08:51.565 --> 08:53.901
WE'RE OUT
OF ICE CREAM.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.877
DO I NEED TO GO GET MOM?

09:03.877 --> 09:06.647
CARMEN, HOW WOULD YOU FEEL

09:06.647 --> 09:08.415
IF YOU SUDDENLY FOUND OUT
YOU WERE ADOPTED

09:08.415 --> 09:09.750
AND I WASN'T YOUR REAL DAD?

09:09.750 --> 09:11.619
DAD, DON'T SAY THAT.

09:11.619 --> 09:15.789
UNLESS YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY
POSITIVE IT'S TRUE.

09:15.789 --> 09:18.458
IT WOULD EXPLAIN SO MUCH!

09:18.458 --> 09:20.093
YOU'RE MINE.

09:20.093 --> 09:22.896
IF YOU WERE ADOPTED, I WOULD
HAVE RETURNED YOU ALREADY.

09:23.897 --> 09:26.166
CALIFORNIA HAS LEMON LAWS.

09:26.166 --> 09:29.002
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

09:35.609 --> 09:37.878
LINDA. COME IN.

09:37.878 --> 09:40.914
I'M SORRY
TO COME OVER SO LATE.

09:40.914 --> 09:44.051
I-I GOT YOUR ADDRESS
OUT OF MAX'S FILE.

09:44.051 --> 09:46.887
BUT I-I HAD TO TALK
TO YOU FACE-TO-FACE.

09:46.887 --> 09:49.122
LOOK, I'M SORRY
ABOUT TONIGHT, ALL RIGHT?

09:49.122 --> 09:50.891
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE
OPENED MY MOUTH.

09:50.891 --> 09:52.726
NO, NO,
I TALKED TO MY PARENTS,

09:52.726 --> 09:54.494
AND THEY TOLD ME
EVERYTHING.

09:54.494 --> 09:57.064
YOU KNOW, I WANTED TO TELL YOU
THE FIRST TIME I MET YOU,

09:57.064 --> 09:58.899
BUT YOU HAD
SUCH A GREAT LIFE.

09:58.899 --> 10:00.300
I DIDN'T WANT
TO MESS THAT UP.

10:00.300 --> 10:01.902
THANKS.

10:01.902 --> 10:05.005
THANKS FOR GIVING ME
ONE MORE GOOD YEAR.

10:07.240 --> 10:09.777
[ Voice breaking ]
GOD, I --

10:09.777 --> 10:11.444
I WOKE UP THIS MORNING,

10:11.444 --> 10:15.783
AND I WAS THE ONLY CHILD
OF TWO LOVING, ITALIAN PARENTS.

10:15.783 --> 10:19.186
NOW IT'S 11:00 P.M.,
AND I'M A MEXICAN.

10:19.186 --> 10:21.288
[ SOBS ]

10:26.459 --> 10:30.030
OH, NO.

10:30.030 --> 10:32.132
YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE REALLY NOT MEXICAN

10:32.132 --> 10:33.934
UNTIL YOU'VE GONE TO A WEDDING
WITH A WHITE DRESS

10:33.934 --> 10:35.703
AND A BLACK BRA UNDER.

10:35.703 --> 10:39.206
IT'S JUST SUCH A SHOCK.

10:39.206 --> 10:41.809
WHAT ARE MY REAL MOTHER
AND FATHER LIKE?

10:41.809 --> 10:45.012
WELL, OUR FATHER'S EASY.

10:45.012 --> 10:47.547
HE RAN OUT ON MOM
BEFORE YOU WERE BORN.

10:47.547 --> 10:49.983
I DIDN'T KNOW HIM, BUT
I TRACKED HIM DOWN LAST YEAR.

10:49.983 --> 10:51.919
I PUNCHED HIM IN THE FACE,

10:51.919 --> 10:55.655
HE ASKED ME FOR A KIDNEY,
AND HE DIED.

10:55.655 --> 10:58.491
AND MY MOTHER?

10:58.491 --> 11:00.127
OH, YEAH.

11:00.127 --> 11:02.963
SHE'S KIND OF HARD TO DESCRIBE
IN JUST A FEW WORDS.

11:02.963 --> 11:06.700
SHE'S A SHORT, BITTER DRUNK.

11:06.700 --> 11:08.301
ACTUALLY,
THAT COVERS IT.

11:10.637 --> 11:13.640
WELL, WHATEVER SHE'S LIKE,
SHE'S STILL MY BIRTH MOTHER

11:13.640 --> 11:15.275
AND I WANT TO MEET HER.

11:15.275 --> 11:18.511
YOU KNOW, LINDA, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

11:18.511 --> 11:20.981
FORGET ABOUT BENNY. YOU AND I
ARE BROTHER AND SISTER.

11:20.981 --> 11:22.349
WE SHOULD GET
TO KNOW EACH OTHER.

11:22.349 --> 11:26.153
OH, YEAH. I WANT TO KNOW
ALL ABOUT YOU, GEORGE,

11:26.153 --> 11:28.055
BUT I HAVE
TO MEET MY MOTHER.

11:28.055 --> 11:31.258
LOOK, I'M TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU, OKAY?

11:31.258 --> 11:33.060
SHE KNOWS
THAT YOU'RE OUT THERE.

11:33.060 --> 11:34.928
BUT WHEN OUR FATHER LEFT,

11:34.928 --> 11:36.997
AND SHE COULDN'T AFFORD
TO RAISE BOTH KIDS, YOU KNOW,

11:36.997 --> 11:39.466
SHE LET YOU GO,
AND WHEN SHE LET YOU GO,

11:39.466 --> 11:41.568
SHE LET YOU GO.

11:41.568 --> 11:44.171
WELL, IF YOU REALLY WANT
TO BE A BROTHER TO ME,

11:44.171 --> 11:47.707
YOU WOULD START
BY INTRODUCING ME TO MY MOM.

11:47.707 --> 11:51.078
[ SIGHS ]
I DON'T THINK SO.

11:51.078 --> 11:53.413
WHY DON'T YOU WANT ME
TO MEET HER?

11:53.413 --> 11:55.348
ARE YOU JEALOUS?

11:55.348 --> 11:59.219
YOU DON'T WANT TO SHARE
YOUR MOTHER WITH ME?

11:59.219 --> 12:01.721
[ LAUGHS ]

12:01.721 --> 12:05.325
SHARE? I'LL TRADE!

12:08.395 --> 12:10.931
I COULD BE ITALIAN.

12:10.931 --> 12:15.135
[ HUMMING ITALIAN TUNE ]

12:15.135 --> 12:17.070
TRY THE CANNOLI!
FORGET ABOUT IT!

12:17.070 --> 12:18.839
I KNOW A GUY!
WA-CHA!

12:18.839 --> 12:21.708
BADA-BING! HO!

12:21.708 --> 12:23.777
THAT'S A STEREOTYPE.

12:23.777 --> 12:25.445
WHAT DO YOU CARE?
YOU'RE A MEXICAN.

12:31.751 --> 12:33.053
[ BENNY SIGHS ]

12:33.053 --> 12:36.890
THAT WAS QUITE
A MEAL, ANGIE.

12:36.890 --> 12:40.193
I'M OFF TO SMOKE THE TASTE OF IT
OUT OF MY MOUTH.

12:44.131 --> 12:45.765
[ YAWNS ]

12:45.765 --> 12:47.734
MAX,
WHY ARE YOU SO TIRED?

12:47.734 --> 12:50.670
I WAS UP TILL 11:00 LAST NIGHT
TRYING TO DO HOMEWORK.

12:50.670 --> 12:52.539
DAD, YOU'RE DYSLEXIC.

12:52.539 --> 12:55.342
HOW DID YOU MAKE IT THROUGH
ALL THE REGULAR CLASSES?

12:55.342 --> 12:58.045
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I REALLY STRUGGLED, MAX,

12:58.045 --> 12:59.947
'CAUSE I DIDN'T HAVE
SOMEBODY TO HELP ME,

12:59.947 --> 13:01.348
BUT YOU DO, SON.

13:01.348 --> 13:04.217
THANKS, DAD.
NOT ME, CARMEN.

13:04.217 --> 13:06.119
HELP YOUR BROTHER
WITH HIS HOMEWORK.

13:06.119 --> 13:07.921
BUT WHY DO I
HAVE TO DO IT?

13:07.921 --> 13:10.190
BECAUSE I'LL GIVE YOU $50
FOR EVERY "B" HE GETS

13:10.190 --> 13:12.292
AND $25 FOR EVERY "C."

13:12.292 --> 13:15.695
WELL, WHAT HAPPENS
IF I HELP HIM GET AN "A"?

13:15.695 --> 13:18.131
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:18.131 --> 13:20.901
THEN I'LL GIVE YOU
A MILLION DOLLARS

13:20.901 --> 13:23.136
AND A RIDE ON A ROCKET SHIP.

13:25.338 --> 13:28.175
YOU KNOW, MAYBE ONCE YOU GET
TO KNOW LINDA BETTER,

13:28.175 --> 13:30.177
SHE CAN HELP US GET MAX
BACK IN SPECIAL ED.

13:30.177 --> 13:33.213
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN, ANGIE.

13:33.213 --> 13:36.416
I DECIDED NOT
TO INTRODUCE HER TO MY MOM.

13:36.416 --> 13:38.185
SO YOU'RE ALREADY

13:38.185 --> 13:40.353
TREATING YOUR SISTER
BETTER THAN YOU TREATED ME?

13:40.353 --> 13:42.890
GOD!

13:44.824 --> 13:46.559
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:48.328 --> 13:49.529
GEORGE.

13:51.631 --> 13:53.266
HI.

13:53.266 --> 13:54.935
LINDA,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

13:58.571 --> 14:00.908
ARE YOU BENNY?

14:02.675 --> 14:04.444
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

14:07.480 --> 14:09.883
I'M YOUR DAUGHTER.

14:11.384 --> 14:13.486
WOW. HEH.

14:13.486 --> 14:17.424
THE THREE OF US HAVEN'T
BEEN TOGETHER SINCE...

14:20.994 --> 14:25.198
...SINCE YOU GAVE HER
AWAY TO STRANGERS.

14:25.198 --> 14:35.408
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
NO?

14:35.408 --> 14:38.078
WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:38.078 --> 14:42.015
UH, YOU KNOW HOW SOMETIMES
STRANGERS COME BY,

14:42.015 --> 14:45.318
AND WE FIND OUT
THEY'RE RELATED TO YOUR DAD?

14:45.318 --> 14:48.321
UH...

14:48.321 --> 14:52.425
UH, THIS IS
ONE OF THOSE NIGHTS. GO.

14:54.161 --> 14:57.197
CARMEN,
THEY FOUND ANOTHER ONE!

15:02.169 --> 15:05.038
THIS REALLY ISN'T
GEORGE'S FAULT.

15:05.038 --> 15:06.539
HE DID TELL ME
TO STAY AWAY.

15:06.539 --> 15:09.142
I -- I FOLLOWED YOU
FROM THE FACTORY.

15:09.142 --> 15:11.178
I'VE JUST BEEN
SITTING IN THE CAR.

15:11.178 --> 15:13.046
I WAS TRYING TO GET UP
THE COURAGE

15:13.046 --> 15:15.315
TO COME IN AND MEET YOU.

15:17.317 --> 15:19.486
YOU SHOULD HAVE
LISTENED TO GEORGE.

15:19.486 --> 15:23.190
I DIDN'T WANT YOU THEN,
AND I DON'T WANT YOU NOW.

15:24.524 --> 15:26.226
[ SIGHS ]

15:26.226 --> 15:28.261
THAT'S OUR MOMMY!

15:28.261 --> 15:30.563
HEY.

15:30.563 --> 15:33.566
YOU JUST CAN'T WALK AWAY.
YOU'RE HER MOTHER.

15:33.566 --> 15:37.570
NO, I'M NOT.
TINA LORENZO'S HER MOTHER.

15:37.570 --> 15:41.608
LOOK, WHY CAN'T YOU
JUST TALK TO HER, HUH?

15:41.608 --> 15:45.545
IF YOU OPEN UP AND YOU SHOW HER
WHAT YOU'RE REALLY LIKE,

15:45.545 --> 15:49.382
I GUARANTEE SHE'LL NEVER WANT
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

15:51.985 --> 15:54.521
SHE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

15:54.521 --> 15:58.125
SHE WANTS TO MAKE ME
FEEL GUILTY,

15:58.125 --> 16:00.627
AND I GOT NOTHING
TO BE SORRY ABOUT.

16:00.627 --> 16:03.163
I COULDN'T KEEP BOTH OF YOU,

16:03.163 --> 16:07.100
BUT I MADE SURE SHE HAD
A GOOD HOME AND NICE PARENTS.

16:07.100 --> 16:08.601
IS THAT
WHAT'S BOTHERING YOU,

16:08.601 --> 16:10.437
DEEP DOWN INSIDE
YOU FEEL GUILTY?

16:10.437 --> 16:12.472
I DON'T NEED TO HEAR THIS
FROM YOU.

16:12.472 --> 16:15.508
LOOK, MY FATHER
WASN'T IN MY LIFE,

16:15.508 --> 16:17.344
AND I ALWAYS FELT LIKE
THERE WAS SOMETHING MISSING

16:17.344 --> 16:19.246
BECAUSE I DIDN'T KNOW HIM.

16:19.246 --> 16:21.948
I'M TELLING YOU, MOM, THAT'S
HOW SHE'S FEELING RIGHT NOW.

16:21.948 --> 16:25.685
I'M NOTHING
LIKE YOUR FATHER WAS.

16:25.685 --> 16:27.754
IF YOU WALK OUT
THAT GATE, YOU ARE.

16:44.637 --> 16:46.539
COME ON, ANGIE,
WHAT'S GOING ON IN THERE?

16:46.539 --> 16:47.607
I DON'T KNOW.

16:47.607 --> 16:49.942
I HAVEN'T HEARD ANYTHING
FOR A WHILE.

16:49.942 --> 16:51.311
IF MY MOM COMES OUT HERE

16:51.311 --> 16:54.114
WITH LINDA'S FEET
COMING OUT OF HER MOUTH,

16:54.114 --> 16:57.317
WE KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

16:57.317 --> 16:59.852
[ GASPS ]
HERE COMES YOUR MOM.

16:59.852 --> 17:02.755
HELLO.

17:02.755 --> 17:04.424
WELL, I'M OUT OF HERE.

17:04.424 --> 17:07.660
HEY, FOR TOMORROW NIGHT'S
PAINFUL REUNION,

17:07.660 --> 17:12.464
MAYBE YOU COULD TRACK DOWN THAT
PEDESTRIAN I RAN OVER IN '97.

17:15.768 --> 17:17.270
I'M GONNA CHECK ON LINDA.

17:17.270 --> 17:19.372
COME ON, MOM,
WAS IT THAT BAD?

17:19.372 --> 17:23.576
YEAH. I REALIZED
I MADE A HUGE MISTAKE.

17:23.576 --> 17:26.445
YEAH, MOM, BUT YOU SAID YOU
COULDN'T KEEP THE BOTH OF US.

17:26.445 --> 17:28.281
I KNOW.

17:32.385 --> 17:33.920
I SHOULD HAVE TAKEN HER.

17:33.920 --> 17:36.289
SHE'S SMART,

17:36.289 --> 17:40.160
SUCCESSFUL,
HELL OF A WOMAN.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.961
YEAH, OF COURSE
SHE TURNED OUT GREAT.

17:41.961 --> 17:44.097
SHE WAS RAISED BY PEOPLE.

17:48.268 --> 17:52.205
HURTS BEING THE UGLY SISTER,
DOESN'T IT?

17:52.205 --> 17:54.574
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:54.574 --> 17:56.843
SO...

17:56.843 --> 17:59.346
WAS MY MOM
EVERYTHING I SAID SHE WAS?

17:59.346 --> 18:01.514
YOU KNOW, ACTUALLY,
AFTER SHE WARMED UP A BIT,

18:01.514 --> 18:04.284
WE HAD A REALLY GOOD
CONVERSATION.

18:04.284 --> 18:07.387
SHE TOLD ME ABOUT HER CHILDHOOD
AND HER DREAMS

18:07.387 --> 18:10.223
AND SHE EVEN
GAVE ME A BIG HUG.

18:13.860 --> 18:15.395
WHAT?!

18:15.395 --> 18:17.564
PLEASE,
SHE BARELY SHOOK MY HAND.

18:17.564 --> 18:20.833
OH,
SHE SHOOK YOUR HAND?

18:22.702 --> 18:24.637
GEORGE, THANK YOU.

18:24.637 --> 18:26.173
I DON'T KNOW WHAT KIND
OF A RELATIONSHIP

18:26.173 --> 18:27.807
I'LL EVER HAVE WITH BENNY,

18:27.807 --> 18:30.243
BUT IT'S GONNA BE REALLY GREAT
TO HAVE A BIG BROTHER.

18:35.848 --> 18:38.451
I'LL LEAVE YOU TWO ALONE
TO CATCH UP.

18:38.451 --> 18:40.487
PLEASE COME AROUND
FOR THE HOLIDAYS

18:40.487 --> 18:43.890
BECAUSE MOST OF THE TIME
IT'S JUST US AND BENNY.

18:43.890 --> 18:46.759
SERIOUSLY...

18:46.759 --> 18:48.228
I NEED YOU THERE.

18:48.228 --> 18:50.797
THE BOOZE ISN'T WORKING
LIKE IT USED TO.

18:53.266 --> 18:57.370
SO...LINDA,
MY FAVORITE SISTER,

18:57.370 --> 19:00.973
YOU KNOW, YOUR NEPHEW MAX
IS A GREAT KID.

19:00.973 --> 19:03.142
SURE NEEDS TO GET BACK
IN THAT SPECIAL-ED CLASS.

19:03.142 --> 19:05.778
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.
I CAN'T HELP YOU.

19:05.778 --> 19:10.450
BUT I JUST HOOKED YOU UP
WITH YOUR REAL MOM.

19:10.450 --> 19:13.320
AND NOW I OWE YOU?

19:13.320 --> 19:15.288
HELL, YEAH, YOU OWE ME!

19:15.288 --> 19:19.492
I WAS THE ONE
WITH THE CRAPPY CHILDHOOD.

19:19.492 --> 19:23.396
ONE TIME I MADE MYSELF
CHOKE ON A HOT DOG

19:23.396 --> 19:25.532
SO MY MOM COULD COME UP
FROM BEHIND ME

19:25.532 --> 19:28.701
AND GIVE ME THE HEIMLICH...

19:28.701 --> 19:32.339
SO I COULD PRETEND
IT WAS A JUST-BECAUSE HUG.

19:35.141 --> 19:38.044
ALL RIGHT, I'LL ARRANGE
FOR MAX TO RETAKE THE TEST.

19:38.044 --> 19:42.181
AND THEN MAYBE HE WON'T DO
AS WELL THIS TIME,

19:42.181 --> 19:46.419
AND THEN I WOULD BE FORCED
TO PUT HIM BACK IN SPECIAL ED.

19:48.221 --> 19:49.622
WOW.

19:49.622 --> 19:54.327
YOU'RE ALREADY HOLDING
ONE OF YOUR OWN BACK.

19:54.327 --> 19:57.664
CONGRATULATIONS, LINDA.
YOU ARE MEXICAN.

20:04.203 --> 20:09.342
GEORGE, I FEEL GUILTY ABOUT
KEEPING MAX UP ALL NIGHT.

20:09.342 --> 20:11.511
HEY, HE'S GOT
TO FAIL THAT TEST, ANGIE,

20:11.511 --> 20:13.680
IF WE WANT TO GET HIM
BACK IN SPECIAL ED.

20:13.680 --> 20:15.982
HEY, MAX,
TIME TO GET TO SCHOOL.

20:15.982 --> 20:17.484
BIG TEST TODAY.

20:17.484 --> 20:19.118
CAN I EAT
SOMETHING FIRST?

20:19.118 --> 20:20.420
WHAT? ARE YOU CRAZY?!

20:20.420 --> 20:22.455
YOU THINK BETTER
ON AN EMPTY STOMACH.

20:22.455 --> 20:24.624
ALBERT EINSTEIN --
BULIMIC, HUH?

20:24.624 --> 20:27.394
NOW, WHAT HAVE
I TAUGHT YOU, MAX,

20:27.394 --> 20:28.961
ABOUT TRUE OR FALSE
QUESTIONS?

20:28.961 --> 20:30.430
THE ANSWER'S ALWAYS FALSE

20:30.430 --> 20:31.831
'CAUSE THE TEST
IS WRITTEN BY THE MAN,

20:31.831 --> 20:34.133
AND THE MAN
NEVER TELLS THE TRUTH.

20:34.133 --> 20:35.468
THAT'S RIGHT.

20:35.468 --> 20:37.604
AND NEVER GO WITH
YOUR FIRST INSTINCT, HUH?

20:37.604 --> 20:39.572
ALWAYS SECOND-GUESS YOURSELF.

20:39.572 --> 20:42.409
NOW, WHO WAS THE FIRST MAN
TO WALK ON THE MOON?

20:42.409 --> 20:43.676
NEIL ARMSTRONG.

20:43.676 --> 20:45.378
SECOND GUESS?

20:45.378 --> 20:47.179
LANCE ARMSTRONG?

20:47.179 --> 20:48.648
THAT'S MY BOY!

20:48.648 --> 20:49.849
I CAN HEAR YOUR STOMACH
GROWLING. YOU'RE READY.
